1 (3) The objectives of this audit must be formulated, defined, and conducted in accordance with
2 industry standards established for auditing as described in 5-13-308.
3 (4) The cost of the audit in whole must be paid for by the judicial branch.
4 (5) The audit must be completed and presented to the legislative audit committee no later than
5 December 15, 2026. Following review by the legislative audit committee, the audit and any audit followup must:
6 (a) be delivered to members of the law and justice interim committee and the section D interim
7 budget subcommittee who shall serve in the 70th legislature; and
8 (b) be posted on the website of the legislative audit division.
9
10 Section 2. Section 5-13-102, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "5-13-102. Definitions. In this chapter:
12 (1) "committee" means the legislative audit committee;
13 (2) "state agency" means all offices, departments, boards, commissions, institutions, universities,
14 colleges, entities created by an order of or subject to supervision by the Montana supreme court, and any other
15 person or any other administrative unit of state government that spends or encumbers public moneys by virtue
16 of an appropriation from the legislature or that handles money on behalf of the state or that holds any trust or
17 agency moneys from any source."
